10/5/99
  Status:
    - Single channel (Divicom, Hits), no RC: OK
    - Single divicom channel with RC: OK, lie after 10 hrs due to PidBuf leak.
    - 2 HITS channels with RC: garbage picture

10/6/99
  Status:
    - 2 Divicom channel with splicing, no RC: OK.
    - 2 Divicom channels with splicing and RC: OK.

  Find a bug in setting edHdl for TR adjustment.  Added a element in PicStat
  to point to the TP containing first byte of TR to fix the bug.


10/7/99
  - 2 HITS channel switching with RC die in about 1 hr.
    Problem: needs to call cleanCutInit() every time a channel is turn ON
             or BG_SPLICE.
    Fix: call cleanCutInit() in procSetPidGrp(), procStartPidGrp() and
         procSwitchPidGrpReq().

  - Potential bug found: when changing channel status, make sure mode is
    changed at appropriate time.  E.g. when turning on from off, change
    mode AFTER all initialization is done.

  - Bug fix: forgot to set bndryPicFnd flag to FALSE for BG channel
    in procSwitchPidGrpReq().

  - Noticed that mpeg2dec will fail if a start code (16 0's) is found when
    decoding a coefficient!  Need to change VLD table to handle this case.
    Fix: added "0000 0000 0000" to make the code tree complete.

  - VLD investigation: old VLD has two flavors: single pass and multiple pass.
    Single pass reads table once, but need hugh table.
    Multiple pass reads table several times, can use small table.

  - See garbage picture on single HITS bitstream also.  Seems the problem is
    for HITS bitstream, not for multiple HITS.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

10/11/99
  - Also seen multiple DSP problem on another DPS card. 

  - Sun simulation show that the rate converted output bitstream has problem
    for single HITS and echoStar bitstreams.

  - HITS bug fixed.  Wrong setup of reg3 in value of r_sizes in initRcRegs().
    a & b - c : b-c will be computed first, then the & operation!

  - Clear trace buffer when loading code.

  - Cleaned up Release directory.  Base version starts with ver. 100.

  - Prevent trace buffer from being overwritten by stopping the monitor
    task when video is stopped.

  - More elegant splice request command which support M:N splicing.


10/12/99
  - Multiple splice channel per DSP successful!
    Can perform 3 set of splices with about 50% CPU load!
    But die in about 20 min.

  - Multiple DSP problem
    Seems like mudule 1 is bad.
    Problem is probably not in PPC, but in FPGA!


10/13/99
  - Fix bug for SUN simulation
  - Improved trace messages.
  - Complete pidFreeBuf checking
  - Verified that the multiple DSP problem is due to hardware bug.
    The multiple DSP test passed with a good DSP card!
  - Found out how to read local clock.  Problem: the msb of the 45 kHz
    clock is still missing from DEMUX.

  - Made tsfilter work


10/14/99
  - 2 HITS splicing without RC test: die after 11 hrs.
    Problem is due to stack overflow of the output Task.

    Stack usage for each task:

          Task		    Left over space (hex)
    ---------------------------------------------
	Bufferer		overflow
	Switcher		f0
	Output			overflow
	RateConv		178
	Control			128
	Splice Control		1d8
	Splice Request		1f8
	Monitor			12c
    
  - Doubled the stack size of Bufferer, Switcher and Output tasks to
    avoid stack overflow problem.

  - Single Divicom channel with RC: 4->3 Mbps works for almost 4 hrs.
    Test terminated. 

  - Audio integrateion: compilation OK.  Linking OK.


10/15/99
  - Splicing with Divicom and HITS with RC pass over night test!
    Run more than 20 hours.

  - Rate conversion input/output buffers should be allocated in CRAM
    instead of DRAM.  This will significantly improve the performance!


