10/19/99
  Harmonic Lightway bitstream test:
    - Rate conversion does not work
    - Splicing: video OK, audio glitches

  Bypass test:
    Divicom without RC: OK
    Divicom with RC:    OK
    HL without RC:      video OK, audio clicks
    HL with RC:         video stall and blackout occasionally
    HITS without RC:    (HITS' AC3 audio not decodable by Tandberg)
    HITS with RC:       (HITS' AC3 audio not decodable by Tandberg)

  - getLocalTime() usage:
    This function is used mainly in printf and in splice request task.
    The only important usage is in switcher_ext.c, where it is called
    in both the procSwitchCancelReq() and procSwitchTimeout() to fill
    out the actSpliceTime field.  If we redefine the meaning of this
    field then there should be no problem about the missing MSB in the
    33-bit 90 kHz clock.


10/20/99
  - Found that the problem with HITS is due to the use of wrong mux.

  - Relocate rate conversion input/output buffer from DRAM to CRAM.
    Reduction in CPU load can be observed (10-20%).


10/22/99
  - Noticed a big problem in peek():  Data may not be word aligned.
    Therefore peek() may need to access more than two words to gather
    32 bits!

  - Another serious bug in reader: assumes getBits() needs to access only
    2 words at most.  Some TP can actually contains 1 byte of payload!

  - One pathological case for reader to fail is to have some TPs containing
    less than one word of payload.  To handle this case without making
    reader too complication, we can have a compromised approach:
    Assume functions like getBits() or peek() will always be fulfilled with
    at most one buffer refill.  In case a TP containning less than one
    word of payload is encountered, we modify the refill function so that
    more than sufficients TPs will be read to accumulate at least one word
    of data.  The accumulated data will be put at the front of the TP buffer
    containing the last TP being examined.

  - noticed that we actually don't need prefetchFlag in Reader, since
    refill will change curPtr and endPtr also.  This means we will not
    issue a refill call.
    Actually we still need it, and in nextWord we need to check this flag.


